<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>have egg on one’s chin • have egg on one’s face</xh5><p> <i>have egg on one’s chin</i>—(euph.) used as a caution to a man having his trouser zip undone: After the game John came up to the bar with his flies undone. “You <u>have egg on your chin</u>, John,” said Gus.</p><p> <i>have egg on one’s face</i>—(coll.) look foolish; be embarrassed: Gallacher has had some difficult tasks being in Opposition, and he has <u>had egg on his face</u> on a number of occasions.</p> </entry>
